@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'MLink' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your
Workbench must have at least 8 colours.

NOTE: As I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that MLink runs fine
      on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with a
      68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  The game consists of 15 coloured chainlinks that have been
randomly shuffled. You have to place these chainlinks in the right
order, obviously with the top ones (the upper 'semicircles') at the
top, the lower ones (the lower 'semicircles') below and the
intermediate links in between. Of course their colour must match
in each column.

  Note that you don't have to place the chains in a specific colour
order from left to right and the shorter chain can be placed either
in the upper or lower position in its column, as long as its links
are joined together.

  Playing with MLink is very simple: just click on one of the
arrows, each of these arrows will move one (or more) chainlink
tile(s) in that direction.

  The arrows pointing to the right or left will move all the tiles
on that row by one position in the direction indicated (if you move
the tiles to the right, the rightmost tile will go to the left, and
vice-versa if you move the tiles to the left).

  The arrows pointing up and down are always located on the column
where the empty space is positioned, so clicking on one of these
arrows will move a tile up or down to the empty space, if that move
is possible.

  Have fun!

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub}
button.

  To quit the game, click on the game window's close button or by
pressing on the 'Esc' key.

